  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WCS COVID Crisis Response BAM</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed financing package in Banco Agromercantil de Guatemala S.A. (BAM or the Bank), the fourth largest private commercial bank in Guatemala, consists of an investment of up to US$40 million under IFCs COVID 19 Working Capital Solutions (WCS) Crisis Response Facility to support/expand the Banks working capital and traded-related lending program to Guatemala micro small and medium-sized enterprises (MSMEs) as result of the COVID 19 pandemic.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By supporting its clients&apos; capacity to sustain operations during this acute shock, IFC best positions the private sector to support the economic recovery process, shortening the time it will take for the most vulnerable to return to their traditional income-earning opportunities.</narrative>
  </description>
